  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7, then take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Chop your <strong>sweet potato[es]</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces and add them<strong> </strong>to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong>, your <strong>ground smoked paprika </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 25 min or until the sweet potato is cooked through and starting to crisp</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1681478551655-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1681478551655-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1681478551655-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1681478551655-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1681478551655-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the sweet potato is cooking, add your<strong> chicken breast portion[s]</strong> to a chopping board and cover with a sheet of <strong>cling film</strong></p><p>Bash the <strong>chicken</strong> with a <strong>rolling pin</strong> until evenly flattened – this is your<strong> chicken escalope[s]</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1681478565515-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1681478565515-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1681478565515-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1681478565515-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1681478565515-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Spread your <strong>chipotle paste</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) over both sides of the <strong>chicken escalope[s]</strong> using the back of a spoon</p><p>Add your <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> to a plate and season with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>– these are your<strong> seasoned breadcrumbs</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>coated chicken</strong> to the <strong>seasoned breadcrumbs </strong>and press firmly to coat evenly all over – this is your <strong>breaded chicken</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1681478569478-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1681478569478-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1681478569478-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1681478569478-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1681478569478-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>breaded chicken</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 5-6 min on each side (cooking for 5? Do this in batches!) or until golden and cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>crispy chipotle chicken</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
